          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Build the base",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the {{vegetable-oil}} in a pan over medium heat. Fry the {{onion}} for 5 minutes. Add the {{garlic}}, {{ginger-root}}, {{curry-powder}}, {{turmeric}}, and {{tomato-puree}} and stir for 1 minute. Transfer to the slow cooker. Add the {{chicken-thighs-boneless}}, {{tinned-tomatoes}}, {{stock-chicken}}, and {{sea-salt-fine}}. Stir to combine. Cook on low for 6 hours, until the chicken is tender. Stir in the {{garam-masala}}, taste, and adjust seasoning.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Fry the curry powder in oil before adding it. Replace curry powder that is more than a year old. It loses potency quickly",
              "cause": "Curry powder not bloomed or brand is old",
              "symptom": "Curry mild and flat-tasting"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Use mild curry powder and add a tablespoon of double cream or yoghurt to the finished dish to calm the heat",
              "cause": "Medium or hot curry powder rather than mild",
              "symptom": "Too spicy for the household"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Reduce the stock to 100 ml. Remove the lid for the last 20 minutes on high to thicken",
              "cause": "Too much stock, or tinned tomatoes were very thin",
              "symptom": "Sauce too watery"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "This is the weeknight family curry that most British households know. The slow cooker version requires 15 minutes in the morning and no further attention. Serve with basmati rice, naan, and mango chutney. Leftovers are excellent the next day with the sauce even thicker and spicier than when first served.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
